%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20enemies%20testify%20against%20him%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20flanked%20by%20a%20team%20of%20lawyers.%20Behind%20him%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-republicans-attended-trump-hush-money-trial-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoliticians%20from%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20paying%20fealty%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Behind%20them%2C%20rows%20and%20rows%20of%20journalists%20sit%20for%20hours%20in%20hard%2C%20weathered%20wooden%20benches%2C%20shifting%20in%20their%20seats%20for%20a%20better%20look.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20this%20day%2C%20a%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20chair%20was%20filled%20with%20a%20succession%20of%20anxious%20New%20Yorkers%20who%20had%20admitted%20to%20their%20crimes.%20They%20were%20there%20to%20get%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20in%20Donald%20Trump's%20hush-money%20trial%2C%20over%20a%20payment%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstormy-daniels-takes-stand-donald-trump-hush-money-trial-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadult%20film%20star%20Stormy%20Daniels%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20known%20not%20to%20sit%20on%20Wednesday.%20While%20the%20judge%2C%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Juan%20Merchan%2C%20is%20currently%20presiding%20over%20arguably%20the%20highest-profile%20criminal%20case%20in%20American%20history%2C%20he%20keeps%20the%20middle%20of%20his%20week%20clear%20for%20Manhattan's%20mental%20health%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20completely%20different%20world.%20For%20Trump's%20trial%2C%20journalists%20and%20members%20of%20the%20public%20spend%20hours%20lining%20up%20outside%20the%20court%2C%20hoping%20to%20snag%20a%20seat%20in%20the%20courtroom%20or%20in%20a%20spillover%20room%20where%20they%20watch%20the%20proceedings%20on%20large%20TV%20screens.%20Hundreds%20are%20turned%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20two%20recent%20Wednesdays%20at%20the%20mental%20health%20court%2C%20in%20the%20same%20%3Cspan%3Elinoleum-tiled%3C%2Fspan%3E%2015th-floor%20courtroom%20during%20the%20trial's%20off%20days%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20Business%20Insider%20reporter%20was%20the%20only%20journalist%20there.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20these%20Wednesday%20defendants%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20no%20less%20high.%20They%20have%20effectively%20won%20the%20lottery%20to%20be%20offered%20another%20chance%20and%20avoid%20time%20in%20prison.%20It%20is%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20respects%2C%20Merchan%20is%20his%20same%20old%20self%20in%20these%20sessions.%20He%20moves%20briskly%20and%20is%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-lawyer-court-behavior-consequences-manhattan-criminal-hush-money-trial-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20alert%20for%20lawyerly%20evasiveness%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20other%20ways%2C%20Merchan%20carries%20a%20different%20attitude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20plays%20the%20role%20of%20a%20strict%20headmaster%20in%20Trump's%20trial%2C%20holding%20high%20standards%20and%20keeping%20all%20the%20lawyers%20and%20witnesses%20on%20track.%20After%20a%20month%20of%20testimony%2C%20jurors%20will%20begin%20deliberating%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22trump%20cameras%20manhattan%20courtroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650e364239fda2da6cb9bc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20photographed%20in%20a%20packed%20courtroom%20during%20his%20criminal%20hush-money%20trial.%3Cp%3ECurtis%20Means%20-%20Pool%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-hit-gag-violation-judge-threatens-jail-time-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheld%20Trump%20in%20contempt%2010%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20violating%20his%20gag%20order%20and%20threatened%20jail%20time%2C%20remaining%20vigilant%20after%20the%20former%20president's%20lawyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-lawyer-scolded-bigly-after-botched-hush-money-delay-bid-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etried%20numerous%20attempts%20to%20delay%20the%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20(and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-first-felony-trial-hush-money-stormy-daniels-april-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esucceeding%20once%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20mental%20health%20court%2C%20though%2C%20Merchan%2C%20who%20has%20presided%20over%20felony%20criminal%20trials%20since%202009%2C%20is%20more%20like%20a%20kindly%20uncle.%20He%20appears%20to%20genuinely%20want%20everyone%20to%20succeed.%20When%20a%20defendant%20shares%20a%20promising%20update%2C%20he%20cheers%20them%20on.%20When%20he%20chides%2C%20he%20does%20it%20gently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKeep%20it%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20defendants%20who%20give%20updates%20showing%20their%20lives%20are%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20definitely%20turned%20it%20around%20since%20the%20last%20time%20I%20saw%20you%2C%20and%20I'm%20very%20glad%20to%20see%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recently%20told%20one%20defendant%20after%20their%20lawyer%20said%20their%20client%20was%20improving%20after%20a%20rocky%20start%20to%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20has%20such%20good%20news%20to%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weather%20outdoors%20during%20two%20recent%20sessions%20was%20warm%2C%20but%20Merchan%20blasted%20the%20air%20conditioning%2C%20keeping%20the%20courtroom%2C%20which%20Trump%20derisively%20calls%20%26quot%3Bthe%20icebox%2C%26quot%3B%20chilly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20day%2C%20a%20court%20employee%20wore%20a%20heavy%20black%20parka%20that%20reached%20past%20her%20knees.%20The%20hangers%20on%20the%20courtroom's%20coat%20rack%20remained%20untouched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20defendant%20living%20in%20a%20treatment%20facility%20was%20caught%20with%20a%20contraband%20nicotine%20vape%20pen%20under%20her%20pillow.%20She%20was%20unable%20to%20get%20her%20usual%20prescription%20medications%20because%20her%20therapist%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomputer%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Merchan%20appeared%20let%20down%2C%20but%20remained%20sympathetic%20rather%20than%20skeptical%2C%20as%20some%20other%20judges%20might%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20the%20woman%20opened%20up%20to%20him%20about%20her%20depressive%20struggles%20to%20get%20out%20of%20bed%2C%20to%20go%20to%20group%20treatment%20sessions%2C%20or%20do%20much%20of%20anything.%20She%20was%20frozen%20with%20anxiety%20when%20she%20thought%20about%20the%20future%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20be%20honest%20with%20you%2C%20your%20honor%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20doing%20too%20great.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESitting%20high%20above%20her%20at%20the%20bench%2C%20Merchan%20expressed%20his%20own%20frustrations%20about%20the%20world's%20unfairness%20and%20told%20her%20she%20didn't%20need%20to%20apologize%20for%20anything.%20The%20pressure%20of%20the%20future%20she%20was%20feeling%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20really%20the%20pressure%20of%20the%20responsibility%20she'll%20have%20for%20her%20own%20life%20once%20she%20graduates%20from%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20future%20is%20going%20to%20be%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20ready%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20was%20still%20firm%2C%20reminding%20her%20that%20nicotine's%20addictive%20nature%20could%20put%20her%20back%20on%20the%20wrong%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20shouldn't%20be%20doing%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20need%20to%20move%20past%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20is%20strong%2C%20and%20she%20can%20do%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20agree%2C%26quot%3B%20Merchan%20responded%2C%20beaming%2C%20before%20moving%20on%20to%20the%20next%20defendant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211b37eac-4b51-4426-a88c-00c15e56316b%5C%22%3EGetting%20accepted%20is%20just%20the%20start%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Manhattan%20mental%20health%20court%20is%20one%20path%20available%20to%20those%20who%20plead%20guilty%20to%20felonies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFew%20are%20able%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20is%20the%20sole%20judge%20of%20the%20mental%20health%20court%20in%20all%20of%20Manhattan%2C%20and%20has%20presided%20over%20it%20since%20its%20founding%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F01%2F01%2Fnyregion%2Fnew-york-veterans-court.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHe%20is%20also%20the%20only%20judge%20overseeing%20another%20specialized%20court%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20which%20caters%20to%20veterans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20historically%20had%20a%20smaller%20caseload.%20Other%20specialized%20courts%20focus%20on%20defendants%20dealing%20with%20substance%20abuse%20issues%20and%20human%20trafficking.%20An%20Alternatives%20to%20Incarceration%20program%2C%20the%20largest%20diversion%20program%20in%20the%20borough%2C%20is%20also%20available%20as%20something%20of%20a%20catch-all%2C%20offering%20a%20holistic%20approach%20to%20criminal%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one's%20ever%20come%20out%20of%20prison%20better%20than%20they%20went%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Eliza%20Orlins%2C%20a%20New%20York%20City%20public%20defender%20who%20has%20represented%20several%20defendants%20in%20the%20mental%20health%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecourt%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20if%20there%20are%20things%20that%20we%20can%20do%20to%20help%20people%20rather%20than%20just%20punish%20them%2C%20obviously%20it's%20much%2C%20much%20better%20for%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22juan%20merchan%20manhattan%20judge%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650e171a961b37edf39dffa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20York%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Juan%20M.%20Merchan%20posing%20in%20his%20chambers.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSeth%20Wenig%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mental%20health%20court%20has%2056%20ongoing%20cases%20in%20various%20stages%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Manhattan%20District%20Attorney's%20Office%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20figure%20represents%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20the%20thousands%20of%20felony%20cases%20it%20brings%20each%20year.%20Defendants%20need%20to%20demonstrate%20they%20have%20a%20history%20of%20mental%20illness%20and%20might%20need%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%20about%20their%20past%20traumas.%20If%20the%20office%20allows%20it%2C%20a%20mental%20health%20court%20treatment%20plan%20can%20become%20part%20of%20their%20plea%20agreement%2C%20which%20includes%20different%20consequences%20for%20failures.%20And%20once%20that's%20hammered%20out%2C%20Merchan%20needs%20to%20accept%20the%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20hard%2C%20a%20huge%20burden%20to%20even%20get%20so%20far%20as%20to%20be%20accepted%20into%20mental%20health%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Orlins.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20just%20the%20start%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20Merchan%20approves%20to%20enter%20the%20program%2C%20he%20refers%20defendants%20to%20a%20psychiatrist%2C%20who%20then%20comes%20up%20with%20an%20individualized%20plan%20to%20address%20mental%20health%20and%20potential%20substance%20abuse%20issues.%20Often%2C%20it%20involves%20living%20in%20a%20mental%20healthcare%20treatment%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defendants%20check%20in%20every%20few%20weeks%2C%20and%20if%20they%20complete%20the%20program%20to%20the%20Merchan's%20satisfaction%2C%20the%20indictment%20is%20dismissed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20they%20commit%20new%20infractions%20or%20don't%20successfully%20complete%20the%20program%2C%20they%20can%20be%20hit%20with%20the%20recommended%20sentence%20in%20their%20plea%20agreement%2C%20which%20can%20mean%20time%20in%20state%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22juan%20merchan%20empty%20courtroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650e3d2a961b37edf39e102%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJuan%20Merchan's%20empty%20courtroom%2C%20called%20Part%2059.%3Cp%3EANGELA%20WEISS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202014%20and%202021%2C%20300%20individuals%20were%20referred%20to%20the%20Manhattan%20mental%20health%20court%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office.%20In%20that%20time%2C%20190%20were%20accepted%20into%20the%20program.%20Of%20them%2C%20100%20participants%20graduated%2C%20a%20process%20that%20typically%20takes%20between%2012%20and%2024%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecovering%20from%20mental%20health%20episodes%2C%20Orlins%20said%2C%20is%20simply%20hard.%20Not%20everyone%20can%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20theory%2C%20they're%20good.%20And%20if%20people%20are%20successful%2C%20sure%2C%20great.%20But%20it's%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20declined%20an%20interview%20request%20for%20this%20story%2C%20telling%20Business%20Insider%20he%20couldn't%20set%20aside%20any%20time%20during%20the%20ongoing%20Trump%20trial.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Ftrump-hush-money-criminal-trial-judge-merchan-c227f5eab200cccffb19ed931b4dac92%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interview%20with%20the%20Associated%20Press%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20the%20trial%20began%2C%20he%20said%20the%20mental%20health%20court%20let%20him%20%26quot%3Bsee%20people%20through%20a%20different%20lens%26quot%3B%20than%20he%20did%20while%20presiding%20over%20only%20ordinary%20criminal%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227579c873-314d-49d9-a8d7-c6a4fed31b3b%5C%22%3E'If%20you%20are%20ever%20struggling%20and%20having%20a%20hard%20time%2C%20just%20speak%20up'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20might%20have%20a%20dozen%20cases%20each%20morning%2C%20spending%20as%20little%20as%20a%20few%20minutes%20on%20each%20defendant.%20The%20appearances%20look%20different%20than%20a%20normal%20criminal%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20prosecutors%20and%20defense%20attorneys%2C%20there%20are%20case%20managers%2C%20standing%20at%20the%20lectern%20where%20lawyers%20normally%20question%20witnesses%2C%20who%20give%20updates%20about%20how%20each%20defendant%20is%20progressing%20in%20their%20mental%20health%20treatment%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20defendant%20has%20a%20story.%20Merchan%20listens%20carefully%2C%20looking%20directly%20at%20them%20and%20giving%20his%20full%20attention.%20When%20their%20lawyers%20make%20a%20request%2C%20he%20covers%20his%20hand%20with%20his%20mouth%2C%20as%20he%20often%20does%20during%20the%20Trump%20trial%2C%20a%20tic%20for%20when%20he%20is%20thinking%20about%20how%20to%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20recent%20Wednesday%2C%20Merchan%20accepted%20one%20man's%20plea%20and%20inducted%20them%20into%20the%20mental%20health%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20now%20in%20Manhattan%20mental%20health%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWelcome.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20ever%20struggling%20and%20having%20a%20hard%20time%2C%20just%20speak%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20offered%20in%20a%20friendly%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20defendant%20seemed%20like%20he%20would%20be%20headed%20for%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20%26quot%3Babsconded%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20his%20lawyer%2C%20after%20telling%20his%20chaperone%2C%20%26quot%3BSorry%20man%2C%20I%20need%20to%20see%20my%20wife%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20slipping%20away.%20No%20one%20could%20find%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20far%20as%20we%20know%2C%20he%20doesn't%20have%20a%20wife%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22juan%20merchan%20courtroom%20sketch%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650e20aa961b37edf39e037%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20sketch%20of%20Merchan%20presiding%20in%20his%20courtroom.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FJane%20Rosenberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20manager%20seemed%20to%20tear%20up%20a%20little.%20The%20backlog%20of%20people%20trying%20to%20get%20into%20the%20defendant's%20treatment%20facility%20was%20long.%20And%20so%20even%20if%20he%20returned%2C%20he%20wouldn't%20be%20allowed%20back%20in.%20If%20you%20fail%20the%20mental%20health%20court%20program%20in%20such%20a%20dramatic%20fashion%2C%20the%20next%20step%20can%20be%20a%20sentencing%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20allowed%20law%20enforcement%20to%20go%20after%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBench%20warrant%20entered%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20solemnly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20woman%20appearing%20before%20the%20judge%20had%20a%20more%20upbeat%20update.%20She%20spends%20an%20hour%20reading%20every%20day%20and%20recently%20subscribed%20to%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal's%20weekend%20section%2C%20her%20lawyer%20said.%20She%20befriended%20a%20woman%20named%20Iris%20at%20her%20local%20library%2C%20who%20helps%20her%20interpret%20sports%20statistics%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMerchan%20was%20encouraged.%20The%20future%20held%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20like%20to%20adjourn%20the%20case%20for%20graduation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20which%20would%20be%20held%20on%20June%2026.%20It%20would%20be%20long%20after%20Trump%20had%20left%2C%20to%20return%20only%20for%20a%20possible%20sentencing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20was%20the%20last%20case%20scheduled%20to%20be%20heard%20that%20day.%20But%20before%20everyone%20gathered%20their%20belongings%2C%20there%20was%20one%20more%20matter%20to%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20tall%2C%20elderly%2C%20lanky%20lawyer%20had%20approached%20the%20well.%20He%20had%20a%20client%20who%20graduated%20from%20the%20program%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20said%2C%20during%20which%20the%20client%20enrolled%20in%20business%20school.%20The%20client%20was%20now%20set%20to%20graduate%20from%20school%20and%20was%20seeking%20a%20job%2C%20and%20was%20worried%20that%20having%20the%20case%20on%20the%20books%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20the%20indictment%20was%20dismissed%20%E2%80%94%20would%20hurt%20his%20employment%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECould%20the%20judge%20seal%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prosecutors%20didn't%20object.%20%26quot%3BThe%20case%20is%20sealed%2C%26quot%3B%20Merchan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTell%20him%20I%20said%20hello%20and%20wish%20him%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Merchan%20said%2C%20smiling%20warmly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-judge-juan-merchan-manhattan-mental-health-court-wednesday-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716714181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6650bf2fa961b37edf39c35c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-judge-juan-merchan-manhattan-mental-health-court-wednesday-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20he's%20not%20overseeing%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20hush-money%20trial%20on%20Wednesdays%2C%20the%20judge%20presides%20over%20Manhattan's%20mental%20health%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40businessinsider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-judge-juan-merchan-